<subSubSection pageId="462" pageNumber="463" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="462.[810,1452,1023,1729]" pageId="462" pageNumber="463">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,939,1023,1049]" pageId="462" pageNumber="463">Etymology</emphasis>
. The name of the new species honours its discoverer, Shigeko Ooishi.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[863,1223,1091,1118]" pageId="462" pageNumber="463" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="462.[810,1452,1023,1729]" box="[863,1223,1091,1118]" pageId="462" pageNumber="463">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[863,1001,1091,1117]" pageId="462" pageNumber="463">Description</emphasis>
: see 
<bibRefCitation author="Ooishi, S." box="[1059,1218,1091,1117]" journalOrPublisher="Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory" pageId="462" pageNumber="463" pagination="303 - 325" part="19" refId="ref330320" refString="Ooishi, S. (1972) Notodelphyid copepods associated with compound ascidians in Akkeshi Bay, Japan. Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory, 19 (5), 303 - 325. https: // doi. org / 10.5134 / 175727" title="Notodelphyid copepods associated with compound ascidians in Akkeshi Bay, Japan" type="journal article" year="1972">Ooishi (1972)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="462" pageNumber="463" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="462.[810,1452,1023,1729]" pageId="462" pageNumber="463">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[863,972,1125,1151]" pageId="462" pageNumber="463">Remarks</emphasis>
. The specimens described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ooishi, S." journalOrPublisher="Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory" pageId="462" pageNumber="463" pagination="303 - 325" part="19" refId="ref330320" refString="Ooishi, S. (1972) Notodelphyid copepods associated with compound ascidians in Akkeshi Bay, Japan. Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory, 19 (5), 303 - 325. https: // doi. org / 10.5134 / 175727" title="Notodelphyid copepods associated with compound ascidians in Akkeshi Bay, Japan" type="journal article" year="1972">Ooishi (1972)</bibRefCitation>
under the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Kerschner" authorityName="Kerschner" authorityYear="1879" box="[1095,1361,1159,1186]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="462" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uncinata">
<emphasis box="[1095,1115,1160,1185]" italics="true" pageId="462" pageNumber="463">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1135,1233,1160,1185]" italics="true" pageId="462" pageNumber="463">uncinata</emphasis>
Kerschner
</taxonomicName>
exhibit significant differences from the original description and from our observations of typical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kerschner" authorityYear="1879" box="[1221,1362,1228,1254]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="462" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uncinata">
<emphasis box="[1221,1241,1228,1253]" italics="true" pageId="462" pageNumber="463">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1264,1362,1228,1253]" italics="true" pageId="462" pageNumber="463">uncinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These differences are: (1) the caudal ramus is shorter, 2.3 times longer than wide compared to 3.2 times in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kerschner" authorityYear="1879" box="[1309,1444,1296,1321]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="462" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uncinata">
<emphasis box="[1309,1444,1296,1321]" italics="true" pageId="462" pageNumber="463">D. uncinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; (2) the first exopodal segment of leg 2 bears an inner seta (cf. seta absent); (3) the distal segment of the endopod of leg 4 is armed with 3 setae (cf. no setae); and (4) the protopodal process (“outer lobe” according to Ooishi) of leg 5 is produced and tapering. The material examined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ooishi, S." box="[845,1002,1499,1526]" journalOrPublisher="Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory" pageId="462" pageNumber="463" pagination="303 - 325" part="19" refId="ref330320" refString="Ooishi, S. (1972) Notodelphyid copepods associated with compound ascidians in Akkeshi Bay, Japan. Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory, 19 (5), 303 - 325. https: // doi. org / 10.5134 / 175727" title="Notodelphyid copepods associated with compound ascidians in Akkeshi Bay, Japan" type="journal article" year="1972">Ooishi (1972)</bibRefCitation>
is not conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kerschner" authorityYear="1879" box="[1271,1403,1500,1526]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="462" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uncinata">
<emphasis box="[1271,1291,1500,1525]" italics="true" pageId="462" pageNumber="463">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1305,1403,1500,1525]" italics="true" pageId="462" pageNumber="463">uncinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and we here recognize it as a new species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[1247,1451,1533,1559]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="462" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ooishiae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1247,1451,1533,1559]" italics="true" pageId="462" pageNumber="463">Doroixys ooishiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,906,1568,1594]" pageId="462" pageNumber="463">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[810,906,1568,1594]" pageId="462" pageNumber="463" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ooishi, S." box="[920,1084,1567,1594]" journalOrPublisher="Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory" pageId="462" pageNumber="463" pagination="303 - 325" part="19" refId="ref330320" refString="Ooishi, S. (1972) Notodelphyid copepods associated with compound ascidians in Akkeshi Bay, Japan. Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory, 19 (5), 303 - 325. https: // doi. org / 10.5134 / 175727" title="Notodelphyid copepods associated with compound ascidians in Akkeshi Bay, Japan" type="journal article" year="1972">Ooishi (1972)</bibRefCitation>
described the third endopodal segment of leg 1 as bearing 7 setae (formula 1, 2, 4), such an armature formula is extremely unusual for the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1853" box="[810,993,1669,1695]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="462" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Notodelphyidae</taxonomicName>
. This armature condition is considered an abnormality and requires confirmation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
